# Anti-Duplication Rules

## Pre-Generation Checklist — Run Before Writing Any JSX

Ask yourself these questions before writing a single line:

1. Does this look like a section title with a label above it? → Use `SectionHeader`
2. Does this look like a contact form? → Use `GetInTouchForm`
3. Does this look like an expandable FAQ list? → Use `FAQAccordion`
4. Does this look like a product card with an image? → Use `ProductCard`
5. Does this look like a card with an icon + title + description? → Use `ServiceCard`
6. Is this a detail/sub-page that needs a back link? → Use `BackButton`
7. Does this look like a row of numbers/stats? → Use `StatsBar`

If the answer to any of these is yes — import the component, do not rebuild it.

---

## Shared Components Registry

### `src/components/ui/SectionHeader.jsx`
**Use for:** Any section with a centered small label + large heading + optional subtitle.
**Props:** `label`, `title`, `subtitle?`, `align?` (default: `"center"`)

```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT
import SectionHeader from '@/components/ui/SectionHeader';
<SectionHeader label="Our Services" title="What We Do?" subtitle="We provide..." />

// ❌ WRONG — never rebuild this inline
<div className="text-center">
  <span className="text-blue-500 text-sm">Our Services</span>
  <h2 className="text-3xl font-bold">What We Do?</h2>
  <p>We provide...</p>
</div>
```

---

### `src/components/ui/GetInTouchForm.jsx`
**Use for:** The contact form — First Name, Last Name, Phone, Email, Message, Clear + Submit.
**Appears on:** ProductDetail, Products, Services, Inspections, Consultants, Software pages.

```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT
import GetInTouchForm from '@/components/ui/GetInTouchForm';
<GetInTouchForm />

// ❌ WRONG — never rebuild form markup on any page
<form>
  <input placeholder="First Name" />
  ...
</form>
```

---

### `src/components/ui/FAQAccordion.jsx`
**Use for:** Any expandable FAQ list with chevron toggle.
**Props:** `items` (array of `{ question: string, answer: string }`)

```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT
import FAQAccordion from '@/components/ui/FAQAccordion';
import { serviceFaqs } from '@/data/faqs';
<FAQAccordion items={serviceFaqs} />
```

---

### `src/components/ui/ProductCard.jsx`
**Use for:** Any product card with image + name + category label.
**Props:** `id`, `image`, `name`, `category`, `to`

```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT
import ProductCard from '@/components/ui/ProductCard';
import { products } from '@/data/products';
{products.map(p => <ProductCard key={p.id} {...p} />)}
```

---

### `src/components/ui/ServiceCard.jsx`
**Use for:** Any card with icon + title + description.
**Props:** `icon`, `title`, `description`, `href?`

```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT
import { ServiceCard } from '@/components/ui/ServiceCard';
<ServiceCard icon={<SomeIcon />} title="Consultants" description="..." />
```

---

### `src/components/ui/BackButton.jsx`
**Use for:** The `← Back` navigation link shown at the top of all detail/sub-pages.

```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT
import BackButton from '@/components/ui/BackButton';
<BackButton />
```

---

### `src/components/ui/StatsBar.jsx`
**Use for:** A horizontal row of highlight stats (e.g. 30%, 99.9%, <1s, 50+).
**Props:** `stats` (array of `{ value: string, label: string }`)

```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT
import StatsBar from '@/components/ui/StatsBar';
<StatsBar stats={[{ value: '30%', label: 'Energy Reduction' }]} />
```

---

### `src/components/common/Navbar/Navbar.jsx`
**Never** render `<Navbar>` directly in a page. It is injected by `<MainLayout>`.

### `src/components/common/Footer/Footer.jsx`
**Never** render `<Footer>` directly in a page. It is injected by `<MainLayout>`.

---

## Rules When Writing Any Page Component

1. **Scan this registry first.** Every time. No exceptions.
2. **Never copy-paste JSX between pages.** If two pages need the same block, extract it to `src/components/ui/`.
3. **Never rebuild the form.** `GetInTouchForm` is the single source of truth for all contact forms.
4. **Never rebuild the section header.** `SectionHeader` is the single source of truth.
5. **No array literals in component files.** Any `const items = [...]` inside a `.jsx` file must move to `src/data/`.

---

## Updating This Registry

Every time a new shared component is built and placed in `src/components/ui/`, add it here immediately. This registry is the source of truth that prevents duplication across the entire project.
